{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869470234,"sessionID":"ses_285ee7e16ffeXPwEFZMbtQYFk9","part":{"id":"prt_d7a119ebf0013saQK0qmgx8dVx","messageID":"msg_d7a11912e001800dW6dLQpqne0","sessionID":"ses_285ee7e16ffeXPwEFZMbtQYFk9","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_dc33e49153ae4dd8b27cf8d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** sdk-python  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (T001-T008)\n13: \n14: - [ ] **T001** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n15:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n16:   - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n17:   - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T002** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` constructor\n20:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n21:   - *Verify:* Accepts `router_url`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`\n22:   - *Test:* Instantiate client, verify default values\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T003** Implement base URL construction from router components\n25:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n26:   - *Verify:* When no explicit base_url, constructs `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\")`\n27:   - *Test:* Verify correct URL format with various inputs\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T004** Add SESSION_HEADER class constant\n30:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n31:   - *Verify:* `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n32:   - *Test:* Assert class constant equals expected value\n33: \n34: - [ ] **T005** Implement `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` method\n35:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n36:   - *Verify:* POSTs JSON payload to base URL with session header\n37:   - *Test:* Mock HTTP, verify POST request format and headers\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T006** Implement `close()` method\n40:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n41:   - *Verify:* Closes HTTP session\n42:   - *Test:* Call close, verify session closed\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T007** Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` with AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n45:   - *File:* `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n46:   - *Verify:* Exports `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n47:   - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n48: \n49: - [ ] **T008** Add unit tests for AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n50:   - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n51:   - *Verify:* Constructor, URL construction, invoke, close methods tested\n52:   - *Test:* pytest runs successfully\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient (T009-T019)\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T009** Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n59:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n60:   - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeClient`\n61:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n62: \n63: - [ ] **T010** Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` with router URL validation\n64:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n65:   - *Verify:* Accepts `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`, `verbose`, `session_id`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`; validates router_url from arg or ROUTER_URL env var\n66:   - *Test:* Instantiate with valid router_url; test ValueError when missing\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T011** Implement session bootstrap via GET request\n69:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n70:   - *Verify:* When session_id not provided, GET invocation URL and extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n71:   - *Test:* Mock GET response with session header; test ValueError when header missing\n72: \n73: - [ ] **T012** Implement reuse of provided session_id (skip bootstrap)\n74:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n75:   - *Verify:* When session_id provided, use it directly without bootstrap\n76:   - *Test:* Instantiate with session_id, verify no bootstrap GET made\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T013** Initialize AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n79:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n80:   - *Verify:* Creates AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient instance with correct params\n81:   - *Test:* Verify dp_client is set after init\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T014** Implement context manager `__enter__` and `__exit__`\n84:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n85:   - *Verify:* `__enter__` returns self, `__exit__` calls `close()`\n86:   - *Test:* Use client in `with` block, verify close called on exit\n87: \n88: - [ ] **T015** Implement `invoke(payload, timeout)` method\n89:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n90:   - *Verify:* Delegates to dp_client.invoke, raises ValueError if session_id not initialized\n91:   - *Test:* Call invoke with valid session; call with None session_id\n92: \n93: - [ ] **T016** Implement default timeout handling in invoke\n94:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n95:   - *Verify:* When timeout=None, uses (connect_timeout, self.timeout) tuple\n96:   - *Test:* Mock request, verify timeout tuple\n97: \n98: - [ ] **T017** Implement custom timeout in invoke\n99:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n100:   - *Verify:* When timeout is provided, uses provided value\n101:   - *Test:* Invoke with timeout=60, verify timeout passed correctly\n102: \n103: - [ ] **T018** Implement `close()` method\n104:   - *File:* `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n105:   - *Verify:* Closes data plane client and HTTP session\n106:   - *Test:* Call close, verify resources cleaned up\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T019** Update `agentcube/__init__.py` to import from agent_runtime.py\n109:   - *File:* `agentcube/__init__.py`\n110:   - *Verify:* `from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient` in __all__\n111:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient`\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ### Phase 3: Integration Tests & Examples (T020-T023)\n116: \n117: - [ ] **T020** Write unit tests for AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n118:   - *File:* `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py`\n119:   - *Verify:* Constructor, context manager, bootstrap, invoke tested\n120:   - *Test:* pytest runs successfully\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T021** Create example usage script\n123:   - *File:* `examples/agent_runtime_example.py`\n124:   - *Verify:* Demonstrates AgentRuntimeClient usage patterns\n125:   - *Test:* Script runs without syntax errors\n126: \n127: - [ ] **T022** Run full package import test\n128:   - *Verify:* All exports work correctly\n129:   - *Test:* `from agentcube import AgentRuntimeClient; from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n130: \n131: - [ ] **T023** Run linter/typecheck on new code\n132:   - *Verify:* No linting errors\n133:   - *Test:* ruff/ruff check and mypy pass\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Dependencies\n138: \n139: | Task | Depends On |\n140: |------|------------|\n141: | T002 | T001 |\n142: | T003 | T002 |\n143: | T004 | T001 |\n144: | T005 | T003, T004 |\n145: | T006 | T001 |\n146: | T007 | T001, T005 |\n147: | T008 | T001-T007 |\n148: | T010 | T009 |\n149: | T011 | T010, (T001-T007 for dp_client) |\n150: | T012 | T010 |\n151: | T013 | T011 |\n152: | T014 | T013, T018 |\n153: | T015 | T013 |\n154: | T016 | T015 |\n155: | T017 | T015 |\n156: | T018 | T013 |\n157: | T019 | T009, T010 |\n158: | T020 | T009-T019 |\n159: | T021 | T009-T019 |\n160: | T022 | T007, T019 |\n161: | T023 | T001-T022 |\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Verification Checklist\n166: \n167: - [ ] AC001: AgentRuntimeClient constructs with proper defaults (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout)\n168: - [ ] AC002: AgentRuntimeClient creates session via GET when session_id not provided\n169: - [ ] AC003: AgentRuntimeClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n170: - [ ] AC004: AgentRuntimeClient handles missing session header during bootstrap with ValueError\n171: - [ ] AC005: AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n172: - [ ] AC006: invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy\n173: - [ ] AC007: invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload\n174: - [ ] AC008: invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header\n175: - [ ] AC009: invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None\n176: - [ ] AC010: invoke() uses custom timeout when provided\n177: - [ ] AC011: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n178: - [ ] AC012: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant\n179: - [ ] AC013: close() closes the requests.Session\n180: - [ ] AC014: Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap\n181: \n182: ---\n183: \n184: ## References\n185: \n186: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md`\n187: - Design: `python-sdk/design.md` (AgentRuntimeClient sections)\n188: - Spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n189: - Related: AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient implementation)\n\n(End of file - total 189 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient Tasks\n\n**Module:** sdk-python  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (T001-T008)\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n  - *Verify:* File created with class `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n  - *Test:* `from agentcube.clients import AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n- [ ] **T002** Implement `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.__init__` constructor\n  - *File:* `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775869470198,"end":1775869470231}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775869470250,"sessionID":"ses_285ee7e16ffeXPwEFZMbtQYFk9","part":{"id":"prt_d7a11a265001TkOLhOLM36t4Vg","messageID":"msg_d7a11912e001800dW6dLQpqne0","sessionID":"ses_285ee7e16ffeXPwEFZMbtQYFk9","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_0d9ceadac81d435fbabacf54","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-028\n10: - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Background\n18: \n19: Building upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n20: 1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)\n21: 2. Invoke tools via the Agent Runtime data plane with JSON payloads\n22: 3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Requirements\n27: \n28: ### AR-028-001: AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle\n29: \n30: The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or bootstraps a new session via GET on the invocation endpoint, then initializes `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-A — Context manager cleanup\n33: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is used as a context manager\n34: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n35: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `close()`, which closes the underlying `requests.Session`\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-B — Router URL required\n38: - **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n39: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__` runs\n40: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: AR-028-001-C — Constructor parameters with defaults\n43: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n44: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n45: - **THEN** it SHALL set `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `verbose=False`, `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ### AR-028-002: Session bootstrapping\n50: \n51: The system SHALL bootstrap or reuse `session_id` from the Agent Runtime invocation endpoint via `GET` on the base invocation URL.\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: AR-028-002-A — Bootstrap session id\n54: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is not provided\n55: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n56: - **THEN** it SHALL `GET {router}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` and read header `x-agentcube-session-id`\n57: - **AND** if the header is missing, raise `ValueError` with message `Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id`\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: AR-028-002-B — Reuse existing session_id\n60: - **GIVEN** `session_id=\"existing-session-123\"` is provided to constructor\n61: - **WHEN** initialization runs\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL skip session bootstrapping and use the provided session_id directly\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ### AR-028-003: Invoke method\n67: \n68: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` method that POSTs JSON payloads to the data plane with session header.\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-A — Invoke without session\n71: - **GIVEN** `session_id` is falsy (None or empty)\n72: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=None)` is called\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\")`\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-B — Invoke with payload\n76: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized with valid session\n77: - **WHEN** `invoke(payload={\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}, timeout=None)` is called\n78: - **THEN** the client SHALL POST to `{base_url}` with JSON body `{\"tool\": \"calculator\", \"input\": {\"expression\": \"2+2\"}}`\n79: - **AND** headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` and `Content-Type: application/json`\n80: - **AND** return the response from the data plane\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-C — Invoke timeout tuple\n83: - **GIVEN** `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n84: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n85: - **THEN** `timeout` SHALL be `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` where `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: AR-028-003-D — Invoke with custom timeout\n88: - **GIVEN** `invoke(payload, timeout=60)` is called\n89: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n90: - **THEN** read timeout SHALL be `60` seconds\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ### AR-028-004: Data Plane Client URL Construction\n95: \n96: The `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` SHALL construct the base URL from router components.\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-A — Base URL from router components\n99: - **GIVEN** `router_url=\"https://router.example.com\"`, `namespace=\"prod\"`, `agent_name=\"my-agent\"`\n100: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated without `base_url`\n101: - **THEN** it SHALL construct `base_url` as `https://router.example.com/v1/namespaces/prod/agent-runtimes/my-agent/invocations/`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: AR-028-004-B — Explicit base URL\n104: - **GIVEN** `base_url=\"https://custom.example.com/api\"` is explicitly provided\n105: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is instantiated\n106: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided `base_url` directly\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ### AR-028-005: Session Header\n111: \n112: All data plane requests SHALL include the session ID header.\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: AR-028-005-A — Session header on requests\n115: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` is initialized with `session_id=\"session-123\"`\n116: - **WHEN** `invoke` is called\n117: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: session-123`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-028-005-B — Session header constant\n120: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` class\n121: - **WHEN** inspected\n122: - **THEN** it SHALL have class constant `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ### AR-028-006: Close method\n127: \n128: The system SHALL provide a `close` method to clean up resources.\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: AR-028-006-A — Close releases resources\n131: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` has an active session\n132: - **WHEN** `close()` is called\n133: - **THEN** the underlying `requests.Session` SHALL be closed\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Non-Requirements\n138: \n139: The following are explicitly out of scope for this AR:\n140: - Code interpretation functionality (covered in AR-027)\n141: - WebSocket connections for streaming (future enhancement)\n142: - Authentication beyond JWT token (handled by ControlPlaneClient)\n143: - Tool implementation (provided by runtime)\n144: - File operations directly on AgentRuntimeClient (different use case)\n145: - Tool discovery endpoints (list_tools, get_tool_schema) - not in base spec\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Dependencies\n150: \n151: | Dependency | Description |\n152: |------------|-------------|\n153: | AR-027 | CodeInterpreterClient implementation provides the foundation for client patterns |\n154: | python-sdk/design.md | Base SDK design document |\n155: | python-sdk/spec.md | Base specification with AgentRuntimeClient requirements |\n156: | router/api.md | Data plane API specification |\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## Acceptance Criteria\n161: \n162: | ID | Criterion | Verification Method |\n163: |----|-----------|---------------------|\n164: | AC-001 | AgentRuntimeClient constructs with default parameters (agent_name, namespace, timeout, connect_timeout) | Unit test |\n165: | AC-002 | AgentRuntimeClient raises ValueError when router_url missing | Unit test |\n166: | AC-003 | Context manager properly closes resources | Integration test |\n167: | AC-004 | Bootstrap session id via GET reads x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n168: | AC-005 | Missing session header during bootstrap raises ValueError | Unit test with mock |\n169: | AC-006 | Reusing provided session_id skips bootstrap | Unit test with mock |\n170: | AC-007 | invoke() raises ValueError when session_id is falsy | Unit test |\n171: | AC-008 | invoke() makes correct HTTP POST with JSON payload | Unit test with mock |\n172: | AC-009 | invoke() includes x-agentcube-session-id header | Unit test with mock |\n173: | AC-010 | invoke() uses timeout tuple (connect_timeout, self.timeout) when timeout=None | Unit test with mock |\n174: | AC-011 | invoke() uses custom timeout when provided | Unit test with mock |\n175: | AC-012 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components | Unit test |\n176: | AC-013 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient has SESSION_HEADER class constant | Unit test |\n177: | AC-014 | close() closes the requests.Session | Unit test with mock |\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Test Strategy\n182: \n183: 1. **Unit Tests**: Test each method in isolation with mocked HTTP responses\n184: 2. **Integration Tests**: Test against mock server or test environment\n185: 3. **Error Handling Tests**: Verify proper exception handling for network errors, timeouts, and API errors\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ## Implementation Notes\n190: \n191: - Follow the same patterns established in AR-027 (CodeInterpreterClient)\n192: - AgentRuntimeClient has simpler lifecycle than CodeInterpreterClient (no control plane session management)\n193: - The `invoke` method is the primary way to interact with Agent Runtime\n194: - Use the utility modules (http, log, utils) created in AR-027\n195: - Maintain consistency with the exception hierarchy defined in AR-027\n\n(End of file - total 195 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-028 — SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `AgentRuntimeClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to invoke Agent Runtime workloads through the Router (data plane) after bootstrapping a session.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-028\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`, `changes/AR-027` (CodeInterpreterClient foundation)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nBuilding upon the `CodeInterpreterClient` implementation in AR-027, the AgentCube Python SDK requires an `AgentRuntimeClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Agent Runtime sessions through the Router (bootstrap session)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775869470201,"end":1775869470247}}}}
